Subject: Commodore Announces Winners of 4000 Reasons Contest
Status: R

The "Commodore Amiga 4000 Reasons Contest" is now over. The winning entries, as selected
by a panel of judges, are:

GRAND PRIZE: Amiga 4000 with 1960 monitor
WINNER: Eugene T. Cottle
REASON: "Since it was first introduced, the Amiga has been a pioneer. While IBM users
anticipate the next innovation, Amiga owners are already using it."

SECOND PRIZE: Amiga 600HD with 1084S monitor
WINNER: Michael Fontana
REASON: "Used a MAC at school! Used an IBM at work. Bought an Amiga for home. To use it
is to choose it!"

THIRD PRIZE (TIE): AmigaVision Professional
WINNER: David Klinkowize
REASON: "By using Amiga's audio/video applications, I started, at age fourteen, DWK
Productions, my own video business, which will finance my college tuition."

WINNER: Mike Savin
REASON: "It's Advanced, Mind-blowing, Incredible, Graphics and Animation Has 
              Awakened My Imagination Genius, and Artistry!
           My AMIGA is an Astonishing Mesmerizing Indispensible Genuine Amiga (friend)!"
(Mike prepared his entry quite artistically). 

There were over 2,500 entries . . . some humorous, some technical . . . descriptive, graphic
and on and on.

Commodore Business Machines, Inc. sincerely thanks all participants for their time and efforts
with this contest!

